text: It’s true that the UK system didn’t work for me and thus I was fortunate enough to look elsewhere, observing the differences I experienced HOWEVER the requirement to WANT RECOVERY didn’t change because I flew abroad. 💭 Whether in South Africa or in the UK - no treatment can recover for you. Only YOU are able to choose to engage and find what fits for YOU! 🫵🏻 By no means has my disorder just disappeared, but I truly attribute so much of my journey to being a result of REACHING OUT for help. I hope, no matter what location you find yourself, you reach out.  I AM SO LUCKY to have had the opportunity to be treated abroad in such an incredible facility. A MASSIVE thank you goes out to may parents, friends and my team for supporting my decision to seek treatment away. It was truly life-changing. 🌟 If you would like to try a couple of theraputic tools I took from my time away, I created a FREE NOTION TEMPLATE linked in my bio. Using these tools outside of the clinic has been KEY for me. 🔑 It all about finding what works for you, 🥹 Happy Healing, Hatts xxxxx  #grwm #storytime #recovery #edsheeranrecoveryy #treatment #nhs #uk #southafrica #healing #healingjourney

musicMeta/musicName: ik what its like to feel different
text: it’s honestly both shocking n relieving to look back to even 5 months ago and see how far i have come in my own growth and process as a human being. This past October solidified one of the lowest and hardest times of my entire life. That entire span until the new year truely just feels like a cloud of unhappiness and anger with no real memories visible through the pain. If i have learned anything it’s that sometime those self destructive behaviors that feel so incredibly exhilarating in the moment turn out to be the catalyst of your pain. They act as a safety net telling you that “ur okay” when in reality they are the true causes of the pain. Allowing yourself to healthy disconnect from others and not tie their behavior to your emotions was an essential skill i was severely lacking, and one in which i have worked hard over the last couple months to grow.  I had to learn how to love and take care of myself before I could emotionally compensate for anyone else. It was a hard pill to swallow, but truly one of the greatest lessons i’ve learned to date. Healing yourself and working to end damaging lines of trauma is something i hope n pray i continue to manifest every day while simultaneously passing on my experiences to others. Don’t not be afraid to cut out toxic problem behaviors and people from your life. It may feel like ur jumping into free-fall, but i promise you it’s the most impactful thing you can do for yourself.  Learn to love yourself and everything else will fall into place🤗🫶
Posting just to post 🤷‍♀️ Also not that anyone cares but I had the worst month of my entire life mental health wise but I'm doing somewhat better now <3
